Description: Fragment of lip, neck and double handle from a Koan pottery transport amphora. Clay fine, micaceous pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular/ovoid stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription and symbol?
Curator's comments: While there are very good reasons to take all of the stamped handles 1955,0920.1 to 197 as being from Naukratis, a problem arises in this case since it carries a strongly pencilled number '94' and incised '94', both unique among amphora handles from Naukratis. However, site 94 in the area of the temenos of Apollo is a possible reference. No other object is recorded from it, but several from 95 have a similar surface appearance.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0139)
